snippet.textDisplay: not to be a debbie downer, but a lot of animal charities denounce cat cafes, because cats are just not social animals and putting them in a situation where they have to be around a lot of different shelter cats that come and go leads to a lot of stress, not to mention a constant stream of people coming in. Over-grooming is also a real problem because everyone who comes in wants to groom them, and ik we all love cats but ultimately these cats didnt choose to be exploited like this (also notice how the kittens are the only ones full of energy and who want to interact, the adult ones are generally just not happy). We all love cats and want to be around them ik, but think about it like this, would you want your personal pet to have to live like that day in and out? its just not nice.
